stimulus:
Please carefully read the following campaign, and indicate below how much you would donate.

Once you are satisfied, press "Continue" at the bottom.

responses: {"Q0":"Jason has lymphoma, which is a type of cancer that requires months of chemotherapy. His friend is trying to raise money to help Jason out any way he can. Any amount helps, if you can donate."}
{"Q0":"To see statistics on who is willing to donate money to people who have cancer on a go-fund-me related site, based on age, gender, education levels. "}

{"Q0":"I would look into how much more donations one would receive, if they expanded incentives to bake sales, t shirt design sales (using Redbubble or Threadless), and family fun night events. I feel like less people are willing to donate to those with cancer, when it's on a go-fund-me page or they're asking for money donations in the middle of a busy street, whereas if these same people asked for donations with additional incentives for donors, they'd see a higher number of donations coming their way. "}
